  "text": "While the absence of a DPP demonstrates defects in the structure of the rhabdomeres, optical neutralization gives additional information on the nature of the defects. Dissected fl y heads are mounted on a slide. If fl ies express a GFP-tagged protein, fl uorescence can be used. Otherwise, one can make use of bright light microscopy for fl ies with pigmented eye. Fluorescence microscopy using a water immersion objective can be performed with living fl ies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Alternatively, heads are cut off from the fl ies and immersed in oil on a slide, covered with a coverslip, and viewed using an oil immersion objective (63×) (N. Gurudev, personal communication).",
